I"é<p><a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/language-models-are-few-shot-learners">Few-shot learning is directly based on text generation</a>. The link is so strong that <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/few-shot-regime-enables-extreme-customization">few-shot learning</a> can be seen as merely a repurposing of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/iterated-pruning-is-a-light-weight-approach-to-nudging-text-generation">text generation</a>, an application. This seems to be an instance of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/sprandels-portrays-exaptation">exaptation</a> in <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/second-brains-are-like-conceptual-genomes">technology</a>, just like in evolutionary biology.</p>
